How to download Python Dash

Things to download:
1. Python (if you don't already have it)
2. Conda (again, if you don't already have it. If you downloaded the initial data using command prompt, you probably already have this too)
3. Dash (in the command line, type pip install dash)

Suggested things to download:
4. Pandas (if you don't already have it. Type pip install pandas into the command line)
4. JupyterLab (pip install jupyterlab in command line)
5. Jupyter Notebook (pip install notebook in command line)

To launch JupyterLab, type jupyter lab in command line. This will pull up your lab. 
Using JupyterLab rather than Python itself to run Dash allows you to test everything out before committing. 
I find that committing changes too often slows down my computer, so I prefer working in JupyterLab until I have a product that I'm satisfied with.

